## How Dimensional Priorities Shift Across Stages

While all five dimensions remain relevant throughout the maturity journey, their **relative criticality** shifts as agencies evolve:

### Rising & Striving (Early Stages)
**High Priority:**
- Financial Resilience (cash flow stability, margin clarity)
- Market Position (positioning, pipeline, portfolio balance)
- Operational Systems (workflow standardization, early documentation)

**Emerging Priority:**
- Team Structure (role clarity, early delegation)
- Strategic Stewardship (basic planning rhythms)

### Thriving & Driving (Mid-to-Late Stages)
**High Priority:**
- Operational Systems (integration, automation, data visibility)
- Team Structure (leadership depth, culture, performance systems)
- Strategic Stewardship (governance, foresight, capital stewardship)

**Maintained Priority:**
- Financial Resilience (optimization, resilience, reinvestment)
- Market Position (retention, portfolio refinement)

### Arriving (Enterprise Stage)
**High Priority:**
- Strategic Stewardship (continuity, transferability, governance)
- Financial Resilience (capital efficiency, enterprise value)
- Team Structure (succession, distributed leadership)

**Maintained Priority:**
- Market Position (diversification, strategic partnerships)
- Operational Systems (continuous optimization)

This shifting priority ensures that the M+R Audit always guides agencies toward **stage-appropriate focus**—building what's needed now without forcing premature complexity or ignoring critical foundations.

